953
00:56:02,109 --> 00:56:04,862
Like a breath of fresh air.

954
00:56:06,572 --> 00:56:09,075
Really uptight fresh air.

955
00:56:10,618 --> 00:56:13,287
Great head of hair
on the guy though.

956
00:56:14,455 --> 00:56:18,417
This is what's fun too
about being an actor. It's like...

957
00:56:18,793 --> 00:56:22,630
...of course, I know it's you, but
you're disappearing into a character.

958
00:56:22,797 --> 00:56:25,424
It's a really definitive character...

959
00:56:25,591 --> 00:56:29,595
...both in his look and in his attitude,
you know?

960
00:56:29,762 --> 00:56:34,100
It's like, people... I would tell people,
"Oh, yeah. That's J.K. Simmons.

961
00:56:34,267 --> 00:56:36,811
He was in this and that."
"Really? That's the same guy?

962
00:56:36,978 --> 00:56:39,772
Get out of here." You know.

963
00:56:39,981 --> 00:56:41,232
Every copy.

964
00:56:41,774 --> 00:56:47,655
That's the fun part of being the
semi-anonymous character actor...

965
00:56:47,822 --> 00:56:52,451
...to be different all the time.
And that, of course, is...

966
00:56:52,618 --> 00:56:54,495
- ...Ted Raimi...
- Right.

967
00:56:54,662 --> 00:56:58,124
...being abused by his boss,
as he is abused by his older brother...

968
00:56:58,291 --> 00:57:00,042
...the director.

969
00:57:01,002 --> 00:57:02,044
Very much so.

970
00:57:02,211 --> 00:57:05,423
Put an ad on the front page:
"Cash for a picture of Spider-Man."

971
00:57:05,756 --> 00:57:09,218
He doesn't wanna be famous?
I'll make him infamous!

972
00:57:11,804 --> 00:57:16,684
There's the Moondance Diner.

973
00:57:16,851 --> 00:57:19,395
A landmark downtown.

974
00:57:21,397 --> 00:57:25,985
Peter Parker is seeing Mary Jane
for the first time since graduation.

975
00:57:28,487 --> 00:57:31,866
- What are you doing around here?
- Begging for a job. How about you?

976
00:57:32,867 --> 00:57:35,202
These are of course,
all extras that you see...

977
00:57:35,369 --> 00:57:38,789
...despite how crowded
New York can be.

978
00:57:41,375 --> 00:57:44,211
At least in the local area there.

979
00:57:44,378 --> 00:57:46,213
Right. So you have...

980
00:57:47,381 --> 00:57:50,343
...hundreds of people
working crowd control et cetera...

981
00:57:50,509 --> 00:57:52,553
...in New York's finest
and everybody else...

982
00:57:53,054 --> 00:57:56,057
...cordoning off the area,
keeping...

983
00:57:56,807 --> 00:57:58,726
...the fans and the curious onlookers...

984
00:57:58,893 --> 00:58:02,063
<i>wand the photographers,
at cetera, away.</i>

985
00:58:02,229 --> 00:58:04,523
Yeah. With people it's kind of fun...

986
00:58:04,690 --> 00:58:08,527
...you know, because they're excited
about what we're doing...

987
00:58:08,694 --> 00:58:11,572
...and so I kind of like that.

988
00:58:11,739 --> 00:58:17,161
It took me a little getting used to
having several photographers...

989
00:58:18,245 --> 00:58:21,582
...in your eyeline as you're shooting
something, just clicking away.

990
00:58:21,916 --> 00:58:24,293
- That's nice.
- It was disconcerting at first...

991
00:58:24,460 --> 00:58:26,420
...but then I got used to it.

992
00:58:26,587 --> 00:58:29,256
And they try to strike deals
with you too, you know:

993
00:58:29,423 --> 00:58:32,093
"Give me a couple good shots
and I'll leave you alone."

994
00:58:32,259 --> 00:58:34,387
- Yeah? Great.
- Yeah.

995
00:58:36,263 --> 00:58:39,016
Yeah, and then once you do that
for one guy, then you...

996
00:58:39,183 --> 00:58:41,644
Then they're calling all their buddies.

997
00:58:41,811 --> 00:58:44,730
Getting on the paparazzi hotline.

998
00:58:44,897 --> 00:58:46,649
But...

999
00:58:48,609 --> 00:58:54,281
There's Peter being, in her eyes,
supportive and understanding...

1000
00:58:54,448 --> 00:58:56,450
...unlike other people in her life.

1001
00:58:56,617 --> 00:58:58,494
Let's get some lunch some evening.

1002
00:58:58,786 --> 00:59:00,538
And him...

1003
00:59:03,290 --> 00:59:06,836
...still being affected
and infatuated by her...

1004
00:59:07,628 --> 00:59:10,005
...but just finding out
that he's been deceived...

1005
00:59:10,172 --> 00:59:14,051
...by his roommate-slash-best friend,
Harry Osborn.

1006
00:59:24,437 --> 00:59:26,897
Timing's perfect. Hey.

1007
00:59:27,106 --> 00:59:30,401
Five new contracts. It'll be great.

1008
00:59:32,528 --> 00:59:35,197
Storming Norman's
making his weekly inspection.

1009
00:59:35,448 --> 00:59:38,492
Better than the average
two broke, out-of-work guys'...

1010
00:59:38,659 --> 00:59:40,745
- Apartment?
- ...Manhattan apartment. Yeah.

1011
00:59:40,911 --> 00:59:43,581
Well, there was actually
big discussions about that...

1012
00:59:43,748 --> 00:59:48,669
...and how to do it,
and it was basically decided that...

1013
00:59:48,836 --> 00:59:50,796
...Norman probably owned
the building.

1014
00:59:50,963 --> 00:59:54,216
- Right.
- And gave the apartment...

1015
00:59:54,592 --> 00:59:59,346
...to his son.
And I kept talking to them about...

1016
01:00:00,222 --> 01:00:04,685
You know, and they agreed that it
should be somewhat modest in size...

1017
01:00:04,852 --> 01:00:07,897
...inside, despite its size.
Because it's obviously...

1018
01:00:08,063 --> 01:00:10,816
- ...a pretty nice place for Manhattan.
- Yeah.

1019
01:00:10,983 --> 01:00:13,944
I don't think
I could afford that apartment.

1020
01:00:14,111 --> 01:00:16,572
- Well, not before Spider-Man.
- Right.

1021
01:00:16,739 --> 01:00:19,450
- Maybe after the sequel.
- Yeah, yeah.

1022
01:00:19,909 --> 01:00:23,162
Pete, you're probably looking
for a job now, right?

1023
01:00:23,370 --> 01:00:26,207
Dad, maybe you can help him out.

1024
01:00:26,373 --> 01:00:30,711
- No, I appreciate it, but I'll be fine.
- It's no problem. I'll make a few calls.

1025
01:00:30,878 --> 01:00:35,174
No, I couldn't accept it, sir.
I like to earn what I get. I'll find work.

1026
01:00:35,341 --> 01:00:37,009
I respect that.

1027
01:00:37,718 --> 01:00:39,845
You want to make it
on your own steam.

1028
01:00:40,513 --> 01:00:41,847
That's great.

1029
01:00:42,723 --> 01:00:45,059
What other skills do you have,
Parker?

1030
01:00:45,267 --> 01:00:47,228
I was thinking about photography.

1031
01:00:50,356 --> 01:00:51,607
Hello.

1032
01:00:53,526 --> 01:00:55,820
Let's go! Move it!

1033
01:00:56,987 --> 01:00:58,656
Watch the street!

1034
01:00:59,281 --> 01:01:01,784
- And this was on the backlot.
- I was just gonna say...

1035
01:01:01,951 --> 01:01:05,538
...we didn't block off the New York
streets for this sequence, but...

1036
01:01:06,372 --> 01:01:08,666
...a good re-creation.

1037
01:01:11,252 --> 01:01:14,255
And then all the stuff
in the Spider-Man suit...

1038
01:01:14,421 --> 01:01:17,716
...I had to go back
and loop everything.

1039
01:01:17,883 --> 01:01:21,262
You know, go in the studio
with just a microphone...

1040
01:01:21,679 --> 01:01:24,557
...and say lines to pictures and stuff.

1041
01:01:25,891 --> 01:01:28,853
Crap, crap. Megacrap.

1042
01:01:29,019 --> 01:01:30,771
I'll give you $200 for all of them.

1043
01:01:30,938 --> 01:01:33,649
I was disappointed at the premiere,
they laughed so hard...

1044
01:01:33,816 --> 01:01:36,902
...at the first "crap,"
that they missed "mega crap."

1045
01:01:37,069 --> 01:01:38,112
That's it.

1046
01:01:38,279 --> 01:01:41,073
Obviously a very supportive
audience there that night.

1047
01:01:42,616 --> 01:01:45,160
Give you 300.
That's the standard freelance fee.

1048
01:01:45,327 --> 01:01:47,663
- Tear up page one. Run that photo.
- Headline?

1049
01:01:47,955 --> 01:01:51,250
"Spider-Man, Hero or Menace?
Exclusive <i>Daily Bugle</i> Photos."

1050
01:01:51,750 --> 01:01:56,130
I went and spent couple days hanging
around at the New York Post...

1051
01:01:56,297 --> 01:02:02,303
...soaked up the atmosphere, got the
sense of the big-city newspaper office...

1052
01:02:02,469 --> 01:02:05,472
...and what it's like.
And that line about...

1053
01:02:05,639 --> 01:02:08,601
...how much I'll give you
for the photos was actually...

1054
01:02:09,935 --> 01:02:14,607
...one of the little details
that I gleaned during that process.

1055
01:02:14,773 --> 01:02:18,110
- In terms of what standard fees...?
- What's really the going rate for...?

1056
01:02:18,277 --> 01:02:20,738
And how'd we do?
Is it pretty realistic?

1057
01:02:20,905 --> 01:02:21,947
- We changed it.
- Right.

1058
01:02:22,114 --> 01:02:25,576
Because I think it had originally
been something different in the script.

1059
01:02:25,743 --> 01:02:31,707
And here's Elizabeth Banks,
plays Betty Brant...

1060
01:02:32,791 --> 01:02:34,960
...a classic...

1061
01:02:36,253 --> 01:02:41,008
...Spider-Man relationship
between him and her.

1062
01:02:42,968 --> 01:02:44,970
I'm working with her
again in a movie now.

1063
01:02:45,137 --> 01:02:46,180
- Oh, yeah?
- Yeah.

1064
01:02:46,347 --> 01:02:50,809
- Now, will she be back in sequels?
- I haven't seen the script...

1065
01:02:50,976 --> 01:02:55,189
...but I imagine. I mean, she works at
the Bugle, so she'll at least be there.

1066
01:02:55,356 --> 01:02:57,107
Whether there's
any future with them...

1067
01:02:57,274 --> 01:03:02,571
...I don't know. There's certainly...
Stuff goes on with them in the comics.

1068
01:03:02,738 --> 01:03:06,533
Right. Maybe in the seventh
or eighth sequel, we'll get to that.

1069
01:03:06,700 --> 01:03:08,369
Yes.

1070
01:03:10,204 --> 01:03:14,208
I'm basically planning on semi-retiring.
I'll do a Spider-Man every two years.

1071
01:03:14,375 --> 01:03:16,502
- And that's it.
- Hope that'll pay the mortgage.

1072
01:03:16,669 --> 01:03:18,295
Do a little theater here and there.

1073
01:03:18,462 --> 01:03:19,505
- Sure.
- Yeah, why not?

1074
01:03:19,672 --> 01:03:24,134
And my kids can go to a state school.
You know, I'll be taking it easy.

1075
01:03:25,052 --> 01:03:28,055
And they pull the company
out from under him.

1076
01:03:28,389 --> 01:03:29,723
...With entrenched management.

1077
01:03:29,890 --> 01:03:32,267
The deal is off if you come with it.

1078
01:03:32,434 --> 01:03:35,854
The board expects your resignation
in 30 days.

1079
01:03:36,063 --> 01:03:38,023
You can't do this to me.

1080
01:03:41,193 --> 01:03:43,487
I started this company.

1081
01:03:44,530 --> 01:03:46,949
You know how much I sacrificed?!

1082
01:03:48,158 --> 01:03:49,868
He's starting to crack up a little.

1083
01:03:50,035 --> 01:03:52,705
A little Mr. Hyde coming out there
in Dr. Jekyll.

1084
01:03:52,871 --> 01:03:56,333
Norman, the board is unanimous.

1085
01:03:56,792 --> 01:04:00,796
We're announcing the sale
after the World Unity Festival.

1086
01:04:00,963 --> 01:04:02,464
I'm sorry.

1087
01:04:03,465 --> 01:04:05,592
You're out, Norman.

1088
01:04:07,803 --> 01:04:13,225
I have a feeling these OSCORP guys
are gonna meet an unhappy ending.

1089
01:04:13,392 --> 01:04:16,353
Something dark
is looming in the future.

1090
01:04:16,520 --> 01:04:19,273
They gave him
a little too much information.

1091
01:04:19,440 --> 01:04:23,444
They're gonna announce it
right after the Unity Fest.

1092
01:04:23,610 --> 01:04:27,948
And here we are in Times Square,
Southern California.

1093
01:04:29,116 --> 01:04:30,659
Yes.

1094
01:04:31,660 --> 01:04:35,247
And Peter has his first
non-Spider-Man assignment.

1095
01:04:38,584 --> 01:04:40,669
Macy Gray.

1096
01:04:42,588 --> 01:04:45,549
Coincidentally,
a Columbia recording artist.

1097
01:04:45,716 --> 01:04:47,176
Really?

1098
01:04:47,342 --> 01:04:49,845
- Strange how that happens.
- Yes.

1099
01:04:50,012 --> 01:04:53,265
Funny enough, I was promoting
Spider-Man in Europe...

1100
01:04:54,308 --> 01:04:57,394
...and she was touring in Europe
and I bumped into her...

1101
01:04:57,561 --> 01:05:01,815
...in three different countries
while I was promoting Spider-Man...

1102
01:05:01,982 --> 01:05:06,904
...and I hung out with her a little bit.
